                            <comment id="133424" author="jhammond" created="Fri, 13 Nov 2015 02:35:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Di,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why wasn&apos;t the stupid test disabled 4+ weeks ago?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="130971" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2015 22:56:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree. I also have seen sanity test 300k take out my nodes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="130968" author="di.wang" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2015 22:41:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, after we change OUT_UPDATE_REPLY_SIZE from 16384 to 4096 ( &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/15899&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/15899&lt;/a&gt;),  this problem already bite us, because 4096 is certainly not enough for some big updates operation like  sanity.sh  300k &quot;test large striped directory&quot;.  Simply run &quot;MDSCOUNT=4 ONLY=300 sh sanity.sh&quot; 2/3 times, will cause memory corruption. So this patch needs to get into 2.8. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="130863" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2015 13:56:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alex Zhuravlev (alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/16889&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/16889&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
